Hugo Chavez , the self-declared
socialist who transformed Venezuelan politics by channeling
record oil revenue to the poor, nationalizing corporations and
vilifying foes as U.S. imperialist puppets, has died. He was 58.  To contact the editor responsible for this slideshow:
